<p>I have a user in AD but not in my vip group.  What should I change to prevent that user from authenticating? Only the vip group members should successfully authenticate. </p>  <pre><code>    @Configuration     @EnableWebMvcSecurity     public class WebSecurityConfig extends WebSecurityConfigurerAdapter {         @Configuration         protected static class AuthenticationConfiguration extends GlobalAuthenticationConfigurerAdapter {             @Override             public void init(AuthenticationManagerBuilder auth) throws Exception {                 auth.ldapAuthentication().userDnPatterns("uid={0},CN=vip,CN=Users,DC=test,DC=corp,DC=urlint,DC=net")                         .groupSearchFilter("(uniqueMember={0})").groupSearchBase("ou=groups")                         .groupRoleAttribute("cn").contextSource();             }         }... </code></pre>  <p>A small portion from the ldif ... </p>  <pre><code>memberOf: CN=vip,CN=Users,DC=test,DC=corp,DC=urlint,DC=net sAMAccountName: testuser1 </code></pre>